text: Diane, Dowager Duchess of Württemberg (née Princess Diane Françoise Maria da Gloria d'Orléans; born 24 March 1940) is a French-German painter, sculptor, writer and philanthropist. She was the wife of Carl, Duke of Württemberg, head of the House of Württemberg. She is the fourth daughter and sixth child of Henri, Count of Paris and his wife, Princess Isabelle of Orléans-Braganza. ==References== Category:1940 births Category:Living people Category:French royalty Category:German dukes and duchesses Category:French philanthropists Category:German painters Category:German sculptors Category:German writers Category:German philanthropists Category:People from Petrópolis
